data.description: Welcome home to 3304 Silver Oak Lane in the coveted Buena Creek neighborhood of Vista. Locals have long revered Buena Creek for its large parcels, wide open streets, and the "country feel" located just a few minutes from everything the bustling city center provides.  This ~3,519 square foot home and ~0.62 acre parcel is situated down a long driveway at the end of a cul-de-sac providing added privacy for the owners. In addition, this home has no HOA, no Mello-Roos assessments, and it's location just outside of city limits means the property taxes are slightly lower than many other Vista homes.  The long, private driveway with gated access provides both an element of security and an attractive entrance. The parcel is ideally oriented, so it receives steady sun and natural light most of the day and the backyard faces Southwest, which makes for gorgeous sunsets and outdoor enjoyment all year long.  Inside the home is spacious and well-appointed with a split level floor plan. Most of the living space is on the entry level with the primary bedroom and bath just nine stairs up and a bedroom or bonus room and bath eight stairs down on the lower level. The owners designed this home with quality finishes and materials throughout including real wood built in cabinetry, Italian tile, and designer fixtures. This is a custom home from the ground up.  The kitchen was thoughtfully designed with Italian tile flooring, high quality cherry cabinetry with appliance "garages" including slide out doors and leaded display glass, Dacor 6 burner stove top, built in refrigerator with cabinet panel doors, tons of counter space, a gorgeous hammered copper hood, large granite island, a 9'x6' walk in pantry, dedicated spice storage and a lot more. This kitchen was designed with great attention to detail and is great for entertaining. Don't miss the "service or second kitchen" between the kitchen and garage. This area serves as the laundry room and second kitchen with an extra sink, built in oven, dishwasher, and room for an extra refrigerator and freezer! How convenient!   The primary suite is private and spacious (~800 Sq. Ft. w bath). The location is ideal at the back of the home away from family and guests with a walk out balcony overlooking the backyard. The room is bright and open with light coming in from multiple directions and don't miss the gorgeous wood beamed ceiling. Just off the primary suite on your way to the bath are dual closets, one large walk in and one reach in. The primary bath is spacious, with a walk in shower at the far end, separate tub, dual sinks, and a private toilet.   One feature of the home sure to attract attention is the large downstairs bonus room. The home is currently configured as a 3 bedroom / 3 bath, but this downstairs area was designed with flexibility in mind. The area could be split into two separate spacious bedrooms, each with its own exterior access, making the home a true 4 bedroom(see virtual tour). The area could also be modified into an ADU. It is large enough to frame in a small kitchen and rooms if desired and it already has a dedicated separate entrance.  I love the outdoor space around this home, especially the backyard and deck. The deck area measures ~1,300 square feet with plenty of room for patio tables, games, or even an above ground pool. The private backyard seems to go on forever with numerous spots to explore or just relax in the shade. There is an outbuilding/shop that measures ~12'x24' that will convey with the home.  Additional features include vinyl double glazed tinted windows & sliders, a whole house fan, 3 pull down attic-access stairs, 3 skylights, a spacious 2 car garage, a recirculating solar hot water system and tank, lightweight concrete tile roof, and much more.  3304 Silver Oak Lane is a distinctive home in an incredibly desirable location, and we expect it will sell quickly.
